HEADWORD: Valerianic
<hw>Va*le`ri*an"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or obtained from, valerian root; specifically,
designating an acid which is usually called <xex>valeric
acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
